
Context Root: david-tobrise-tech11-assignment-1.0-SNAPSHOT
Documentation: Ensure you have payara 5 installed and Java 8+
1. Extract the folder
2. cd into the context root:
3. type this command: mvn clean package payara-micro:start

ENDPOINTS:
1. Create a New User
METHOD: POST
Endpoint: localhost:8080/david-tobrise-tech11-assignment-1.0-SNAPSHOT/api/v1/user-resource/new-user
Request Body:
{
	"firstName":"Tome",
	"lastName":"James",
	"email":"tom@gmail.com",
	"password":"jaemy123",
	"birthDate":"1976-04-24"
}
Response: JSON

2. Get a particular User
METHOD: GET
Endpoint: localhost:8080/david-tobrise-tech11-assignment-1.0-SNAPSHOT/api/v1/user-resource/user/3
Response: JSON

3. List All Users
METHOD: GET
Endpoint: localhost:8080/david-tobrise-tech11-assignment-1.0-SNAPSHOT/api/v1/user-resource/users
Response: JSON

4.Delete a User
METHOD: DELETE
Endpoint: localhost:8080/david-tobrise-tech11-assignment-1.0-SNAPSHOT/api/v1/user-resource/delete-user/3
Response: JSON

5. Update a User
METHOD: PUT
Endpoint: localhost:8080/david-tobrise-tech11-assignment-1.0-SNAPSHOT/api/v1/user-resource/update-user/3
Request Body:
{
	"firstName":"Tome",
	"lastName":"James",
	"email":"tom@gmail.com",
	"password":"jaemy123",
	"birthDate":"1976-04-24"
}
Response: JSON



